content:
Automatically analyzes and documents Next.js routes when page files are created or modified. Generates a route map showing all available routes, dynamic segments, and API endpoints.

```json
{
  "PostToolUse": [
    {
      "matcher": "Edit|Write",
      "hooks": [
        {
          "type": "command",
          "command": "if [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *pages/*.js ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *pages/*.tsx ]] || [[ \"$CLAUDE_TOOL_FILE_PATH\" == *app/*page.tsx ]]; then echo '🗺️ Analyzing Next.js routes...' && find ./pages ./app -name '*.js' -o -name '*.tsx' 2>/dev/null | grep -E '(page|route)\\.(jsx?|tsx?)$' | sed 's|^\\./pages||;s|^\\./app||;s|/page\\.(jsx?|tsx?)$||;s|/route\\.(jsx?|tsx?)$||;s|\\[|:|g;s|\\]||g;s|index$|/|' | sort | uniq > routes.txt && echo '📄 Route map updated in routes.txt' && echo '✅ Found '$(wc -l < routes.txt)' routes'; fi"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
